{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-jsx","path":"/Miniconda/02-How-to use-miniconda/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"67628e77-5ba6-5b1f-a8d8-de053de36381","html":"<p>The previous article explains how to properly install and configure Miniconda. This article will explain how to manage your environments.</p>\n<h2>Creating a Virtual Environment</h2>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      conda create --name <myenv> python=<3.7> pip -y\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<p>This command will create a virtual environment with the following properties:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>-name myenv You can choose any name you want here</li>\n<li>python=3.7 you can set the version to be whatever you want such as 2.7 (if you don't specify a version it will choose the latest)</li>\n<li>-y this just preemptively answers yes to creating the environment</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Activating a Virtual Environment</h2>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      conda activate <myenv>\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<h2>Deactivating a Virtual Environment</h2>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      conda deactivate <myenv>\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<h2>Listing Available Environments</h2>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      conda env list\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<h2>Removing an Environment</h2>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      conda remove --name <myenv> --all\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<h2>Cloning an Environment</h2>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      conda create --name <myclone> --clone <myenv>\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<h2>Removing PS1 Prompt</h2>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      conda config --set changeps1 false\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<p>To re-enable:</p>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      conda config --set changeps1 true\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<h2>Searching for packages</h2>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      conda search <package-name>\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<h2>Sharing an environment</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>First export the environment</li>\n</ul>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      conda env export > environment.yml\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<ul>\n<li>Now install in another Anaconda Environment Manager</li>\n</ul>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      conda env create -f environment.yml\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<h2>Installing Packages &#x26; Pinning Versions</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>With conda (=)</li>\n</ul>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      conda install <package>=<version-number>\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<ul>\n<li>With pip (==)</li>\n</ul>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      pip install <package>==<version-number>\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  ","excerpt":"The previous article explains how to properly install and configure Miniconda. This article will explain how to manage your environmentsâ€¦","frontmatter":{"title":"Managing Environments with Miniconda","tags":["miniconda"],"image":{"childImageSharp":{"resize":{"src":"/static/fa7b659b02c579ef29c4beab0d4328f2/9cf42/miniconda.jpg"},"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.7747747747747749,"src":"/static/fa7b659b02c579ef29c4beab0d4328f2/e3fce/miniconda.jpg","srcSet":"/static/fa7b659b02c579ef29c4beab0d4328f2/81890/miniconda.jpg 197w,\n/static/fa7b659b02c579ef29c4beab0d4328f2/b7e42/miniconda.jpg 393w,\n/static/fa7b659b02c579ef29c4beab0d4328f2/e3fce/miniconda.jpg 786w,\n/static/fa7b659b02c579ef29c4beab0d4328f2/16310/miniconda.jpg 1024w","sizes":"(max-width: 786px) 100vw, 786px"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/Miniconda/02-How-to use-miniconda/","prev":{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/Git/01-Merging-Upstream-Repo-Fork/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Merging an upstream repo into your fork","tags":["git"]}}},"next":{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/Jupyter/01-jupyter-remote/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Setting up a Remote Jupyter Lab Server","tags":["jupyter"]}}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3649515864"]}